item.title: Are there any FREE labels to submit music to?
item.dc:creator: Arimyth
item.description:
It sounds like you‚Äôre getting ‚Äúlabels‚Äù and ‚Äúpromo channels‚Äù confused.

Labels are the accounts that will release your song, usually on their account, and should have a demo submissions link on their page, for example:

Promo channels are the accounts that will repost your song, sometimes for a bit of green like you said, and usually don‚Äôt require more than a follow / like on their page to become ‚Äúeligible‚Äù for their promotion. For example:

I personally don‚Äôt go around messaging promo channels (let alone paying for them) because I find them to be a complete waste of time due to the high volume of tracks that they actually promote (your track will get buried almost instantly and it provides no real engagement). I‚Äôd stick to growing your audience in a more organic manner and building up contacts that you know to help promote your music.

item.title: Are there any FREE labels to submit music to?
item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
I‚Äôm no expert at this, but given the climate of the industry, I think you‚Äôd have more success running through repost networks and self promotion. You can release music for free through sites like BandCamp and distributors like Amuse. There‚Äôs a few to choose from.

A label (in the traditional sense) is going to be interested in making money. That‚Äôs what they do, that‚Äôs what they are there for. There‚Äôs quite a lot of people who write music, so it‚Äôs more likely they‚Äôll want to pick up already established artists with a following so that they don‚Äôt have to take a chance paying out of pocket on an unknown. The only advantage I can think of with submitting work to any kind of label as opposed to self releasing is promotion.

I‚Äôve been told getting your music out there is 10% production and 90% promotion. It‚Äôs probably true. I don‚Äôt say all this to discourage you, by all means, I‚Äôd shoot out my work everywhere, but, definitely don‚Äôt PAY UP FRONT that‚Äôs ridiculous. That‚Äôs like paying to have something done around your house in full before the job is even started‚Ä¶
